                <Label Text="Here are some ways to lead a healthier life:" FontSize="40"/>

                <Label FontSize="20">
                    <Label.Text>

                        • Daily physical activity should be increased. Adults are advised to walk for at least half an hour each day. Adolescents are required to engage in outdoor activities for at least 60 minutes each day.
• Nutrients should be consumed in snacks as well as three main meals. Morning breakfast must be done, meals should not be skipped.
• Reduce the amount of oil consumed. Fried foods should not be consumed. Boiling, grilling, steaming and oven cooking methods should be preferred in cooking.
• Select foods with low sugar content; The use of refined sugar and consumption of sugary nutrients should be reduced.
• Salt consumption should be reduced and iodized salt should be used. Brine foods should be avoided.
• Consumption of fresh fruits and vegetables should be increased and care should be taken to consume thoroughly cleaned products.
• The habit of drinking milk must be achieved. Care should be taken to consume calcium-rich milk, cheese and yogurt for bone health.
• At least 8-10 glasses of water should be consumed per day.
• Body weight should be kept at the recommended level.
• Fast food consumption should be reduced.
• Alcohol and cigarettes should not be used." />

                    </Label.Text>
                </Label>
